00040 /*
00041 RAMP will need to instantiate an msdata::RAMPAdapter object, and call it to fill
00042 in the appropriate RAMP structures: 
00043 
00044     using namespace pwiz::msdata;
00045 
00046     RAMPAdapter adapter("something.mzML");
00047 
00048     unsigned int scanIndex = rampAdapter.index(19); // get index for scan 19
00049 
00050     ScanHeaderStruct temp;
00051     adapter.getScanHeader(scanIndex, temp);
00052 
00053     vector<double> buffer; 
00054     adapter.getScanPeaks(scanIndex, buffer);
00055 
00056     RunHeaderStruct temp2;
00057     adapter.getRunHeader(temp2);
00058     
00059     InstrumentHeaderStruct temp3;
00060     adapter.getInstrumentHeader(temp3);
00061 
00062 Note that the MSData library can throw exceptions, so the RAMP code will have to be able
00063 to handle these gracefully.  Another option is to have these RAMPAdapter functions catch
00064 any exceptions and return an error code if something goes wrong.
00065 */

00071     MSData tiny;

00130 void test(const string& filename)
00131 {
00132     RAMPAdapter adapter(filename);
00133 
00134     size_t scanCount = adapter.scanCount();
00135     if (os_) *os_ << "scanCount: " << scanCount << "\n\n";
00136     unit_assert(scanCount == 3);
00137 
00138     unit_assert(adapter.index(19) == 0);
00139     unit_assert(adapter.index(20) == 1);
00140     unit_assert(adapter.index(21) == 2);
00141 
00142     // first scan (scan number == 19)
00143 
00144     ScanHeaderStruct header1;
00145     adapter.getScanHeader(0, header1);
00146     if (os_) *os_ << header1;
00147     unit_assert(header1.seqNum == 1);
00148     unit_assert(header1.acquisitionNum == 19);
00149     unit_assert(header1.msLevel == 1);
00150     unit_assert(header1.peaksCount == 15);
00151     const double epsilon = 1e-8;
00152     unit_assert_equal(header1.totIonCurrent, 1.66755e7, epsilon);
00153     unit_assert_equal(header1.retentionTime, 353.43, epsilon);
00154     unit_assert_equal(header1.basePeakMZ, 445.347, epsilon);
00155     unit_assert_equal(header1.basePeakIntensity, 120053, epsilon);
00156     unit_assert_equal(header1.collisionEnergy, 0., epsilon);
00157     unit_assert_equal(header1.lowMZ, 400.39, epsilon);
00158     unit_assert_equal(header1.highMZ, 1795.56, epsilon);
00159     unit_assert(header1.precursorScanNum == 0);
00160     unit_assert(header1.scanType == string("Full"));
00161 
00162     vector<double> peaks;
00163     adapter.getScanPeaks(0, peaks);
00164     unit_assert(peaks.size() == 30);
00165     if (os_)
00166     {
00167         const MZIntensityPair* begin = reinterpret_cast<const MZIntensityPair*>(&peaks[0]);
00168         copy(begin, begin+15, ostream_iterator<MZIntensityPair>(*os_, "\n"));
00169         *os_ << endl;
00170     }
00171 
00172     // second scan (scan number == 20)
00173 
00174     ScanHeaderStruct header2;
00175     adapter.getScanHeader(1, header2);
00176     if (os_) *os_ << header2;
00177     unit_assert(header2.seqNum == 2);
00178     unit_assert(header2.acquisitionNum == 20);
00179     unit_assert(header2.msLevel == 2);
00180     unit_assert(header2.peaksCount == 10);
00181     unit_assert_equal(header2.totIonCurrent, 1.66755e7, epsilon);
00182     unit_assert_equal(header2.retentionTime, 359.43, epsilon);
00183     unit_assert_equal(header2.basePeakMZ, 456.347, epsilon);
00184     unit_assert_equal(header2.basePeakIntensity, 23433, epsilon);
00185     unit_assert_equal(header2.collisionEnergy, 35, epsilon);
00186     unit_assert_equal(header2.lowMZ, 320.39, epsilon);
00187     unit_assert_equal(header2.highMZ, 1003.56, epsilon);
00188     unit_assert(header2.precursorScanNum == 19);
00189     unit_assert_equal(header2.precursorMZ, 445.34, epsilon);
00190     unit_assert(header2.precursorCharge == 2);
00191     unit_assert_equal(header2.precursorIntensity, 120053, epsilon);
00192     unit_assert(header2.scanType == string("Full"));
00193 
00194     adapter.getScanPeaks(1, peaks);
00195     unit_assert(peaks.size() == 20);
00196     if (os_)
00197     {
00198         const MZIntensityPair* begin = reinterpret_cast<const MZIntensityPair*>(&peaks[0]);
00199         copy(begin, begin+10, ostream_iterator<MZIntensityPair>(*os_, "\n"));
00200         *os_ << endl;
00201     }
00202 
00203     // RunHeader
00204 
00205     RunHeaderStruct runHeader;
00206     adapter.getRunHeader(runHeader);
00207     unit_assert(runHeader.scanCount == 3);
00208     unit_assert(runHeader.lowMZ == 0);
00209     unit_assert(runHeader.highMZ == 0);
00210     unit_assert(runHeader.startMZ == 0);
00211     unit_assert(runHeader.endMZ == 0);
00212     unit_assert_equal(runHeader.dStartTime, header1.retentionTime, 1e-6);
00213     unit_assert_equal(runHeader.dEndTime, header2.retentionTime, 1e-6);
00214 
00215     if (os_)
00216         *os_ << "RunHeader:\n" << runHeader << endl;
00217 
00218     // Instrument
00219     InstrumentStruct instrument;
00220     adapter.getInstrument(instrument);
00221     if (os_)
00222         *os_ << "Instrument:\n" << instrument << endl;
00223 
00224     unit_assert(!strcmp(instrument.manufacturer, "Thermo Finnigan"));
00225     unit_assert(!strcmp(instrument.model, "LCQ Deca"));
00226     unit_assert(!strcmp(instrument.ionisation, "nanoelectrospray"));
00227     unit_assert(!strcmp(instrument.analyzer, "quadrupole ion trap"));
00228     unit_assert(!strcmp(instrument.detector, "electron multiplier"));
00229 }
